(* Phase 5 - head rounds 0-15 composed by cut-points: HEAD16.                *)
(*                                                                           *)
(* HEAD8 scaled to all 16 head rounds (15 inline ENSURES_SEQUENCE_TAC cuts   *)
(* at pc+0xd7/0x142/.../0x6b1), mechanically generated by                     *)
(* orchestrator/logs/session-006-gen.py (N=4 output structurally identical to *)
(* the hand-written HEAD4 - regression-checked).  After 16 rounds the         *)
(* period-8 register rotation realigns to canonical (a->RAX,..,h->R11), the   *)
(* clean seam into rounds_16_xx.                                             *)
(*                                                                           *)
(* ROUND-15 DEFERRED Sigma0 FOLD (verified vs the binary, session 006).      *)
(* Round 15 defers its  add %r14,%rax  (Sigma0 fold completing new-a) PAST    *)
(* the head-exit JMP at orig 0x71d (=pc+0x719): the fold is at orig 0x730 =   *)
(* pc+0x72c.  So at the JMP target RAX would hold only T1+Maj and R14 the     *)
(* Sigma0 addend - a SPLIT new-a.  To land on a clean compress-16 state we    *)
(* step the final segment 37 instrs to pc+0x72f (orig 0x733, just past the    *)
(* fold), absorbing it into RAX.  Between the JMP and 0x730 the rounds_16_xx  *)
(* prologue only loads W[1]/W[14] (slots 0x8/0x70) into scratch r13/r15,      *)
(* copies r13->r12 and rotates r13 by 7; R14 (=Sigma0) is preserved across    *)
(* the JMP, so the fold is exactly  new-a = (T1+Maj) + Sigma0  as the spec     *)
(* wants.  Hence the postcondition RIP is pc+0x72f and every working var       *)
(* equals EL j (sha512_round^16 [a;..;h] ...) with NO split, plus the          *)
(* scratch R12 = word_bytereverse wraw1, R13 = word_ror (br wraw1) 7,          *)
(* R15 = word_bytereverse wraw14, and (CRUCIAL for the Phase-7 seam) the       *)
(* round-15 Maj carry RDI = word_xor (EL 1 ..) (EL 2 ..) of the 16-round nest. *)
(* These extra conjuncts mirror SHA-256's HEAD16 and are exactly what the      *)
(* inner loop's first sub-round consumes; dropping the RDI carry would leave   *)
(* the Phase-7 seam unable to re-derive it (the round31s-union-gap class).     *)
