(* Phase 7 - BODY15: the first FIFTEEN rounds_16_xx sub-rounds (rounds 16..30) *)
(* of one inner pass, composed by 14 cut-points (one per sub-round boundary,  *)
(* clean deferred-Sigma0-fold-to-fold states at fold_pc+3).  Pure scale-up of *)
(* BODY1 via the auditable generator orchestrator/logs/session-008-body-gen.py *)
(* (token-validated at N=1 against the committed SHA512_BLOCK_NOHW_BODY1:      *)
(* identical statement modulo the full ring carry + EL ordering).             *)
(*                                                                           *)
(* Entry pc+0x72f (= HEAD16 exit, round-16 clean entry); exit pc+0x10c6        *)
(* (= sub-round-15 deferred-Sigma0 fold orig 0x10c7 + 3 - 4 = round-30's clean *)
(* exit, with sub-round 15's sigma/Maj scratch already live).  Each segment is *)
(* 47 instructions.  Register rotation / Maj-carry parity / K-walk continue    *)
(* from the head unchanged (round 16 canonical); sub-round i reads K at byte   *)
(* offset koff(i)=32*(i DIV 2)+8*(i MOD 2) relative to kbase (= rbp at round-16 *)
(* entry), period-2 +8/+24 lea stride.  Each sub-round REWRITES one ring slot  *)
(* (i mod 16) in place to the schedule-expansion                              *)
(*   W[16+i] = sigma1(ring[(i+14)%16]) + ring[(i+9)%16]                        *)
(*             + sigma0(ring[(i+1)%16]) + ring[i%16]                          *)
(* and the un-rewritten slots still hold v_j.  The nested sigma expansions     *)
(* scale to 15 segments under WORD_RULE with no per-slot ABBREV needed (only   *)
(* the running working-state rr_{i-1} is abbreviated per segment).            *)
(*                                                                           *)
(* WHY NOT 16: sub-round 15 (round 31) defers its Sigma0 fold to orig 0x10c7,  *)
(* which is PAST the conditional back-edge `jne 0x71f` (sentinel               *)
(* `cmp BYTE PTR [rbp+7],0` at orig 0x115a).  Round 31 has no clean folded     *)
(* state reachable without crossing the (symbolic-kbase) branch; that split    *)
(* tail + the back-edge are the Phase-8 loop-seam's job (analogous to HEAD16   *)
(* stopping at the round-15 pre-fold boundary).  BODY15 is the clean,          *)
(* composable body lemma; it ends where the 15th fold completes and exposes    *)
(* round-31's scratch (R12/R13 sigma0, R15/RDI sigma1+Maj-carry per parity) +  *)
(* RBP=kbase+232 for the seam.                                                 *)
(* ------------------------------------------------------------------------- *)
